element-type.name: commandButton
element-type.description: Extends standard commandButton by user role support.

element-type.name: commandLink
element-type.description: Extends standard commandLink by user role support and the HTML target attribute.

element-type.name: dataTable
element-type.description: Extended data_table that adds some additional features to the standard data_table action: see attribute descriptions for preserveDataModel, sortColumn, sortAscending and preserveSort.

element-type.name: inputHidden
element-type.description: Extends standard inputHidden by providing additional MyFaces goodies.

element-type.name: inputText
element-type.description: Extends standard inputText by user role support.

element-type.name: inputTextarea
element-type.description: Extends standard inputTextarea by user role support.

element-type.name: message
element-type.description: MyFaces extension to the standard messages tag: see summaryDetailSeparator attribute

element-type.name: messages
element-type.description: MyFaces extension to the standard messages tag: see showInputLabel attribute

element-type.name: outputLabel
element-type.description: Extends standard outputLabel by user role support.

element-type.name: outputText
element-type.description: Extends standard outputText by user role support.

element-type.name: panelGroup
element-type.description: Extends standard panelGroup by user role support.

element-type.name: selectOneMenu
element-type.description: Extends standard selectOneMenu by user role support.

element-type.name: selectOneRadio
element-type.description: Extends standard selectOneRadio by user role support. Additionally this extended selectOneRadio accepts a layout attribute of value "spread" (see custom radio tag).

element-type.name: selectManyCheckbox
element-type.description: Extends standard selectManyCheckbox by user role support. Additionally this extended selectManyCheckbox accepts a layout attribute of value "spread" (see custom checkbox tag).

element-type.name: inputCalendar
element-type.description: Provides a calendar.

element-type.name: jsValueChangeListener
element-type.description: Value change listener on client side.

element-type.name: jsValueSet
element-type.description: Setting a value from the model in java-script so that it can be used (e.g. by the value change listener) afterwards.

element-type.name: checkbox
element-type.description: Renders a HTML input of type "checkbox". The associated SelectItem comes from an extended selectManyCheckbox component with layout "spread". The selectManyCheckbox is referenced by the "for" attribute. All HTML pass-through attributes for this input are taken from the associated selectManyCheckbox.

element-type.name: commandNavigation
element-type.description: Must be nested inside a panel_navigation action and renders a clickable navigation item. This action is derived from the standard command_link action and has equal attributes. (Replaces former "navigation_item" tag.)

element-type.name: commandSortHeader
element-type.description: Clickable sort column header. Must be nested inside an extended data_table tag. This tag is derived from the standard command_link tag and has the additional attributes columnName and arrow. Note: In contrary to normal command links the default for the "immediate" attribute is "true".

element-type.name: dataList
element-type.description: Similar to dataTable, but does not render a table. Instead the layout attribute controls how each dataRow is rendered.

element-type.name: dataScroller
element-type.description: Scroller for UIData components eg. dataTable Must be nested inside footer facet of dataTable OR for attribute must be given so that corresponding uiData can be found

element-type.name: inputFileUpload
element-type.description: You must enable the MultiPart Filter to make this component work (see web.xml). Also, don't forget to set the form's attribute "enctype" to "multipart/form-data". See "examples/web/fileupload.jsp" for an example!

element-type.name: inputHtml
element-type.description: An inline HTML based word processor based on the Kupu library. See http://kupu.oscom.org Right now, the support is limited to one editor per page (but you can use tabs to have multiple editors, but only one rendered at a time).

element-type.name: selectOneCountry
element-type.description: A localized list of countries choose box. The value binds to the country ISO 3166 code. This is the same code as for java.util.Locale.getCountry(). The official codes list is available here : http://www.iso.ch/iso/en/prods-services/iso3166ma/02iso-3166-code-lists/list-en1.html

element-type.name: stylesheet
element-type.description: a component, which renders the path to a common CSS-file

element-type.name: div
element-type.description: Places a div around its children

element-type.name: radio
element-type.description: Renders a HTML input of type "radio". The associated SelectItem comes from an extended selectOneRadio component with layout "spread". The selectOneRadio is referenced by the "for" attribute. All HTML pass-through attributes for this input are taken from the associated selectOneRadio.

element-type.name: treeColumn
element-type.description: Renders a HTML input of type "treeColumn". This tag outlines the column where the tree structure will be render as part of the tree table.

element-type.name: treeCheckbox
element-type.description: Renders a HTML input of type "treeCheckbox". The associated comes from the treeCheckbox itemLabel and itemValue. The selected items come from an extended selectManyCheckbox component with layout "spread". The selectManyCheckbox is referenced by the "for" attribute. All HTML pass-through attributes for this input are taken from the associated selectManyCheckbox.

element-type.name: popup
element-type.description: Renders a popup which displays on a mouse event.

element-type.name: newspaperTable
element-type.description: A data table for rendering long skinny tables as short wide table by wrapping the table over a specified number of columns.

element-type.name: aliasBean
element-type.description:
A tag that defines a new bean (alias) with a given value. This allows you to design a subform with a generic (fictive) beans and to include it in all the pages where you use it. You just need to make an alias to the real bean named after the generic bean before including the subform.
When used within an aliasBeansScope tag, this tag adds the alias to the aliasBeansScope. This makes configuration with multiple aliasBeans easier to write.

element-type.name: saveState
element-type.description: saveState enables you to persist beans and values longer than request scope, but shorter than session scope. It is ideal for persisting backing beans and values with the same scope as your view components. It does this by saving the target state with the component tree.

element-type.name: updateActionListener
element-type.description: Registers a org.apache.myfaces.custom.updateactionlistener.UpdateActionListener at the parent component.

element-type.name: validateCreditCard
element-type.description: A custom validator for creditCards, based upons Jakarta Commons.

element-type.name: validateEmail
element-type.description: A custom validator for email address format, based upons Jakarta Commons.

element-type.name: validateRegExpr
element-type.description: A custom validator for reg. expr., based upons Jakarta Commons.

element-type.name: validateEqual
element-type.description: A custom validator for validations against foreign component values.
